(22, 2, '2018-10-04 23:01:39', '2018-10-04 23:01:39', '<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2>Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It!</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"//downloads.mailchimp.com/js/signup-forms/popup/unique-methods/embed.js\" data-dojo-config=\"usePlainJson: true, isDebug: false\"></script><script type=\"text/javascript\">window.dojoRequire([\"mojo/signup-forms/Loader\"], function(L) { L.start({\"baseUrl\":\"mc.us15.list-manage.com\",\"uuid\":\"343d8cd6e346b50a86cc67d1b\",\"lid\":\"6791140e42\",\"uniqueMethods\":true}) })</script></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcome to Brains Stages, where you can find out the latest research and practical tips for raising and educating children <em><strong>in harmony with how their brains develop</strong></em>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":33,\"align\":\"center\",\"width\":402,\"height\":596} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\"><figure class=\"aligncenter is-resized\"><img src=\"https://thebrainstages.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/brainstagescover-exp4-7d-stroke_1_orig.jpg\" alt=\"Brain Stages Cover\" class=\"wp-image-33\" width=\"402\" height=\"596\"/><figcaption>Brain Stages Cover</figcaption></figure></div>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You\'ll find answers to questions in accordance with science such as:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>What can you do to give your child a leg up in today’s competitive society while raising a happy, well-adjusted future adult?</li><li>How can you get a disinterested kid engaged in school and learning? (<em>Hint:</em> It\'s probably not what you think.)</li><li>How can you help an anxious child relax for better learning?</li><li>What sure-fire ways can you help a struggling child get caught up in math or reading — and have FUN while you\'re at it?</li><li>How can you get your gifted child\'s needs met?</li><li>What can you do to help kids develop social skills — even if dealing with people isn\'t <em>your</em> best thing?</li><li>What’s the most effective way to empower children for a successful life? (<em>Hint</em>: This is also probably not what you think.) And much more!</li><li><strong>BONUS: You\'ll find your own skills improving and your views more empowering—right along with your kids!</strong></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://thebrainstages.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/jackie_headshot-2.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"107\" data-link=\"https://thebrainstages.com/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/jackie_headshot-3/\" class=\"wp-image-107\"/><figcaption>Jackie Frischknecht, PhD</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://thebrainstages.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/trish_headshot-1.jpeg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"108\" data-link=\"https://thebrainstages.com/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/trish_headshot-2/\" class=\"wp-image-108\"/><figcaption>Trish Wilkinson, Author and Licensed Educator<br/></figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Jacqueline Frischknecht, PhD and mother of three, and I, Trish Wilkinson, mother of two and veteran teacher, are excited to share with you what we’ve learned through thousands of hours of experience and ongoing research. On the <a href=\"/blog.html\">Brain Stages blog</a>, you\'ll find out how brains work, practical ways to enjoy kids more and stress less, and how to optimize situations as well as solve problems.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even Better, <strong><em>Bra</em><em>in Stages: How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K – 5</em></strong>, our grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years, will be available November 13, 2018 to make your life with kids a lot easier and way more pleasant!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Please consider joining our community of people who want to make the world a better place for kids and parents by clicking the box at the bottom of this page to get exclusive tips.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To learn the surprising way Brain Stages came to be, click <a href=\"/blog/too-much-coincidence-not-to-be-part-of-the-cosmic-plan\">here.</a><br/>To find out more about the <em>Brain Stages</em> book, click <a href=\"/book.html\">here.</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks for visiting!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>-Trish Wilkinson</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-0 is-cropped\"></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->', 'About Brain Stages', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-brain-stages-brain-stages', '', '', '2018-10-13 22:53:28', '2018-10-13 22:53:28', '', 0, 'https://thebrainstages.com/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(23, 2, '2018-10-04 23:01:39', '2018-10-04 23:01:39', '\n	<div class=\"wsite-section-wrap\">\n	<div class=\"wsite-section wsite-body-section wsite-background-21\">\n		<div class=\"wsite-section-content\">\n          <div class=\"container\">\n			<div class=\"wsite-section-elements\">\n				<div><div class=\"wsite-multicol\"><div class=\"wsite-multicol-table-wrap\" style=\"margin:0 -10px;\">\n	<table class=\"wsite-multicol-table\">\n		<tbody class=\"wsite-multicol-tbody\">\n			<tr class=\"wsite-multicol-tr\">\n				<td class=\"wsite-multicol-col\" style=\"width:67.699530516432%; padding:0 10px;\">\n					\n						\n\n<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\">\n<font color=\"#248d6c\">Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It</font><br>\n</h2>\n\n<div class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align:left;\">New brain research comes out almost daily, providing insight as to how kids develop and learn. Brain Stages, in accordance with science, answers questions that so many parents struggle with, such as:<ul>\n<li>What can you do to give your child a leg up in today’s competitive society while raising a happy, well-adjusted future adult?</li>\n<li>How can you get your disinterested kid engaged in school and learning? (<em>Hint:</em> It\'s probably not what you think.)</li>\n<li>How can you help an anxious child relax for better learning?</li>\n<li>What sure-fire ways can you help a struggling child get caught up in math or reading—and have FUN together while you\'re doing it?</li>\n<li>How can you get your gifted kid\'s needs met to stimulate interest in classroom activities?</li>\n<li>How can you help your child develop social skills—even if dealing with people isn\'t <em>your</em> best thing?</li>\n<li>What’s the most effective way to empower your child for a successful life? (<em>Hint</em>: This is also probably not what you think.)</li>\n</ul>\n<br>Though we still have much to grasp about how kids learn, technology has shed considerable light on effective ways to stimulate children’s organic ability to absorb and apply experiences <font color=\"#060606\"><em><font color=\"#000\"><strong>in harmony with how their brains develop</strong></font></em>.</font><br><br>Jacqueline Frischknecht, PhD, and mother of three, and I, Trish Wilkinson, mother of two and veteran teacher, set out to share with you what we’ve learned through thousands of hours of experience and research.<br><br>We hope you enjoy the games, activities, how-tos, and insider information to support school-age kids’ brain development to help ensure their well-being and academic success. Our goal is for your family to have fun together at every age, while you raise smart, happy kids.<br> <br>Even better, you’ll have access to everything we’ve learned in the past 35 years in a much more comprehensive, entertaining, organized fashion this spring 2018, when <a href=\"https://www.sandrajonaspublishing.com/\">Sandra Jonas Publishing</a> releases our book:<br><br><em><strong>Brain Stages: How to Raise Smart, Happy Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K–5</strong></em><br><strong><em>                                        </em></strong><br>Sadly, Jackie passed away before we finished the book. It is my hope that she would be pleased with our <em>Brain Stages</em> website and publication.<br> <br>If you’d like to submit a video of your child doing an activity that you believe could help other parents and kids, or you have helpful information to share, please leave send an email to <a href=\"mailto:trish@thebrainstages.com\">trish@thebrainstages.com</a>.<br><br>We\'d also love for you to join our community of parents, grandparents, caregivers, educators, and other people who want to help make the world a better place by asking questions or writing helpful comments after blog posts.<br><br>Thanks for visiting!<br><br>Trish Wilkinson</div>\n\n<div style=\"text-align:left;\">\n<div style=\"height:0px;overflow:hidden\"></div>\n<span class=\"wsite-social wsite-social-default\"><a class=\"first-child wsite-social-item wsite-social-facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/trish.wilkinson.395?ref=bookmarks\" target=\"_blank\" alt-text=\"Facebook\"><span class=\"wsite-social-item-inner\"></span></a><a class=\"wsite-social-item wsite-social-twitter\" href=\"https://twitter.com/TrishWilkinson\" target=\"_blank\" alt-text=\"Twitter\"><span class=\"wsite-social-item-inner\"></span></a><a class=\"wsite-social-item wsite-social-linkedin\" href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/in/trish-wilkinson-4875646/\" target=\"_blank\" alt-text=\"Linkedin\"><span class=\"wsite-social-item-inner\"></span></a><a class=\"last-child wsite-social-item wsite-social-mail\" href=\"mailto:trish@thebrainstages.com\" target=\"_blank\" alt-text=\"Mail\"><span class=\"wsite-social-item-inner\"></span></a></span>\n<div style=\"height:0px;overflow:hidden\"></div>\n</div>\n\n\n					\n				</td>				<td class=\"wsite-multicol-col\" style=\"width:32.300469483568%; padding:0 10px;\">\n					\n						\n\n<div><div class=\"wsite-multicol\"><div class=\"wsite-multicol-table-wrap\" style=\"margin:0 -15px;\">\n	<table class=\"wsite-multicol-table\">\n		<tbody class=\"wsite-multicol-tbody\">\n			<tr class=\"wsite-multicol-tr\">\n				<td class=\"wsite-multicol-col\" style=\"width:27.920227920228%; padding:0 15px;\">\n					\n						\n\n<div class=\"wsite-spacer\" style=\"height:50px;\"></div>\n\n\n					\n				</td>				<td class=\"wsite-multicol-col\" style=\"width:72.079772079772%; padding:0 15px;\">\n					\n						\n\n<div style=\"text-align:left;\">\n<div style=\"height:0px;overflow:hidden\"></div>\n<span class=\"wsite-social wsite-social-default\"><a class=\"first-child wsite-social-item wsite-social-facebook\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/trish.wilkinson.395?ref=bookmarks\" target=\"_blank\" alt-text=\"Facebook\"><span class=\"wsite-social-item-inner\"></span></a><a class=\"wsite-social-item wsite-social-twitter\" href=\"https://twitter.com/TrishWilkinson\" target=\"_blank\" alt-text=\"Twitter\"><span class=\"wsite-so