oughy+Little+Buffalo%2C+and+Someone+Called+Plastic+&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3AToys+Go+Out%3A+Being+the+Adventures+of+a+Knowledgeable+Stingray%5Cc+a+Toughy+Little+Buffalo%5Cc+and+Someone+Called+Plastic+\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Toys Go Out: Being the Adventures of a Knowledgeable Stingray, a Toughy Little Buffalo, and Someone Called Plastic</em></a> by Emily Jenkins (trilogy)—little girls’ toys and their zany adventures together.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Junie+B.+Jones+series+by+Barbara+Park&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3AJunie+B.+Jones+series+by+Barbara+Park\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Junie B. Jones series by Barbara Park</a>—hilarious, charming character kids love.</li>\n 	<li>Judy Moody series by Megan McDonald—feisty, socially awkward third-grader who usually learns lessons the hard way; great early chapter books with fun illustrations.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Amelia+Bedelia+chapter+book+series+by+Herman+Perish&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3AAmelia+Bedelia+chapter+book+series+by+Herman+Perish\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Amelia Bedelia chapter book series by Herman Perish</a> (nephew of Peggy Perish, author of the picture book series)—entertaining stories that misinterpret idioms and homophones.</li>\n</ol>\n<strong>\nEight Favorite Series of Second Grade Boys (and Girls Too)</strong>\n<ol>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Touchdown+for+Tommy+by+Matt+Christopher&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3ATouchdown+for+Tommy+by+Matt+Christopher\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Touchdown for Tommy</em> by Matt Christopher</a>—author of many books about sporty kids.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Stink+series+by+Megan+McDonald&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3AStink+series+by+Megan+McDonald\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Stink series by Megan McDonald</a>—Judy Moody’s younger brother, a second-grade boy, gets into all kinds of fun predicaments with the best of intentions.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Stink-O-Pedia%3A+Super+Stink-y+Stuff+from+A+to+ZZZZ++Megan+McDonald&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3AStink-O-Pedia%3A+Super+Stink-y+Stuff+from+A+to+ZZZZ++Megan+McDonald\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Stink-O-Pedia: Super Stink-y Stuff from A to ZZZZ</em></a>  also by Megan McDonald—a book of gross facts little boys love.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Super+Super+Smart+Science+Series+by+April+Chloe+Terrazas&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3ASuper+Super+Smart+Science+Series+by+April+Chloe+Terrazas\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Super Smart Science series for kids by April Chloe Terrazas</a>—complicated science concepts explained in a way kids can understand and feel smart.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Nate+the+Great+series+by+Marjorie+Weinman+Sharmat&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3ANate+the+Great+series+by+Marjorie+Weinman+Sharmat\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Nate the Great mystery series by Marjorie Weinman Sharmat</a>—for kids who need practice to get to grade-level reading and like a good whodunit.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Dog+Man+series+by+Dave+Pilkey&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3ADog+Man+series+by+Dave+Pilkey\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Dog Man series by Dave Pilkey</a>—his latest silly series that has kids clamoring for more.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Magic+Tree+House+series+by+Mary+Pope+Osborne&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3AMagic+Tree+House+series+by+Mary+Pope+Osborne\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Magic Tree House series by Mary Pope Osborne</a>—for various reading levels; brings history to life and promotes conversations about historical events.</li>\n 	<li><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/s/ref=nb_sb_noss?url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;field-keywords=Magic+School+Bus+series+by+Joanna+Cole&amp;rh=i%3Aaps%2Ck%3AMagic+School+Bus+series+by+Joanna+Cole\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Magic School Bus series—mostly by Joanna Cole</a>, also various reading levels; entertaining read-along books about science concepts learned through adventure.</li>\n</ol>\n<span style=\"font-size: large;\"><strong>Remember to share this post with your friends. Let\'s get kids reading this summer!</strong></span>\n\n</div>\n<div>\n<div id=\"802094443335514253\" class=\"wcustomhtml\" style=\"width: 100%; overflow-y: hidden;\" align=\"left\"><!-- AddToAny BEGIN -->\n<div class=\"a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 a2a_default_style\"></div>\n<script async=\"\" src=\"https://static.addtoany.com/menu/page.js\"><br />\n</script> <!-- AddToAny END -->\n\n</div>\n</div>', 'Summer Reading to Keep Kids Sharp: Grade 2', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 19:50:03', '2018-10-10 19:50:03', '', 13, 'https://thebrainstages.com/2018/10/10/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(93, 1, '2018-10-10 19:50:23', '2018-10-10 19:50:23', '<div>\n<div class=\"wsite-image wsite-image-border-none\" style=\"padding-top:0px;padding-bottom:30px;margin-left:0px;margin-right:0px;text-align:center\">\n<a><img src=\"http://thebrainstages.com/uploads/1/1/4/0/114011163/published/bs-cover-on-purple2.jpg?1529694136\" alt=\"Picture\" style=\"width:auto;max-width:100%\"></a>\n<div style=\"display:block;font-size:90%\"></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align:left;\">\nWoo-hoo!\n\n<strong>August 28, 2018,</strong> <a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/book.html\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Brain Stages</em></a> will be ready for readers to snap it up and find out lots of insider info and fun, effective ways to nurture kids\' in line with how their brains develop.\n\nYou may have noticed <a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/book.html\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Brain Stages</em></a> has a new cover too. Double-whoo-hoo!\n\n<a href=\"https://www.sandrajonaspublishing.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sandra, independent publisher extraordinaire</a>, revised the original cover with the feedback we received from friends and followers. Thanks so much to those of you who provided observations and suggestions!\n\n<a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/book.html\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Brain Stages</em></a> is a grade-by-grade book, a <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B01DCHZE3A/ref=dp-kindle-redirect?_encoding=UTF8&amp;btkr=1\" target=\"_blank\"><em>What to Expect When You’re Expecting</em></a> for elementary school. The idea is to help create a solid academic, social, emotional, and physical foundation to raise happy, well-adjusted children.\n\n<a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/blog/too-much-coincidence-not-to-be-part-of-the-cosmic-plan\" target=\"_blank\">This project has been in the works for years.</a> But our sources are as up-to-date as you can get. Many cited articles and studies came out <em>this year</em>. I so appreciate Sandra and her crew for allowing me to update things all the way to the deadline to get <em>Brain Stages</em> to the printer for the release of the <a href=\"https://betweenthecoversblog.wordpress.com/2012/01/20/arcs-v-advance-review-copies/\" target=\"_blank\">advance review copies</a> that will be out in mid-July.\n\nNew studies provide ever-greater detail to create an increasingly vivid picture for how children’s brains grow, develop, and learn.\n\nIn turn, I got to add valuable information, games, and activities up to the last second.\n\nSo. Much. Fun.\n\nNot that scientists have brains all figured out. I’m sure lots of new discoveries are on the horizon, and I’ll keep you in-the-know on the Brain Stages blog.\n\n(I’ve developed a sort of obsession with <a href=\"https://www.google.com/alerts\" target=\"_blank\">Google Alerts</a>, to read articles and studies as soon as they’re published.)\n\nAnd Reading <a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/book.html\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Brain Stages</em></a> will make you feel like you’re talking with a trusted friend, a supportive one with answers backed up by the latest intel and thousands of hours of experience.\n\n<a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/book.html\" target=\"_blank\"><em>Brain Stages</em></a> has all kinds of features to save you (or someone you know) time, energy, and anguish to make the child-raising thing a whole lot of fun, such as:\n<ul>\n 	<li>Brain development and function and how to capitalize on meeting children wherever they are in their growth</li>\n 	<li>Social and emotional tendencies at each grade (individuals\' maturity may show up in more than one chapter as no two kids are alike)</li>\n 	<li>Academic expectations in each grade</li>\n 	<li>Ways to keep gifted kids engaged and develop their social skills</li>\n 	<li>How to handle special needs for happier, more successful children</li>\n 	<li>Games that boost mental and physical coordination to enhance creativity, math, language, and thinking abilities — best of all,&nbsp; <em>they make family life more enjoyable and bring relationships closer</em> <span></span></li>\n 	<li>Activities to foster communication skills</li>\n 	<li>Leveled book lists</li>\n 	<li>Tips for quick, healthy nutrition</li>\n 	<li>True stories that are sure to make you laugh, cry, or just give you relief to know you\'re not the only one . . .</li>\n</ul>\nI could go on and on. There\'s so much great stuff!\n\nBut don\'t worry, <em><a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/book.html\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Stages</a></em> is broken into grade-level chapters, kindergarten through fifth, and will have an index to look up things that interest you.\n\nMan, I would\'ve LOVED to have had <em><a href=\"http://thebrainstages.com/book.html\" target=\"_blank\">Brain Stages</a></em> to support my child-raising journey in those early school years.\n\nWe’re living in exciting times!\n\nKids, parents, teachers, and caregivers have all been stressed out trying to keep up with societal expectations.\n\n<font size=\"4\"><em>But less stress, more fun, and better results are right around the corner.</em></font>\n\nHere’s to happier, healthier kids, families, and schools everywhere!\n\n<strong>Please forward this email to your friends, and share the good news on Facebook and Twitter.</strong> Let’s give people something positive to anticipate and celebrate!\n\nLeave a comment if you have something you want to ask or tell us.\n(Maybe tell us what you think of the new cover?)\n\nBest wishes and happy summer!\n\nTrish Wilkinson, co-author\n\n</div>\n<div>\n<div id=\"473363422707327319\" align=\"left\" style=\"width: 100%; overflow-y: hidden;\" class=\"wcustomhtml\">\n<!-- AddToAny BEGIN -->\n<div class=\"a2a_kit a2a_kit_size_32 a2a_default_style\">\n<a class=\"a2a_dd\" href=\"https://www.addtoany.com/share\"></a> <a class=\"a2a_button_facebook\"></a> <a class=\"a2a_button_twitter\"></a> <a class=\"a2a_button_google_plus\"></a> <a class=\"a2a_button_linkedin\"></a></div>\n<script async=\"\" src=\"https://static.addtoany.com/menu/page.js\"><br />\n</script> <!-- AddToAny END -->\n\n</div>\n</div>', '“Brain Stages” Released August 28!', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '15-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 19:50:23', '2018-10-10 19:50:23', '', 15, 'https://thebrainstages.com/2018/10/10/15-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
