(102, 1, '2018-10-10 20:00:55', '2018-10-10 20:00:55', '<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\"><span style=\"color: #248d6c;\">Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It!</span></h2>\n<div class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<p>Welcome to Brains Stages, where you can find out the latest research and practical tips for raising and educating children <span style=\"color: #060606;\"><em><span style=\"color: #000;\"><strong>in harmony with how their brains develop</strong></span></em>.</span></p>\n<p>You\'ll find answers to questions in accordance with science such as:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>What can you do to give your child a leg up in today’s competitive society while raising a happy, well-adjusted future adult?</li>\n<li>How can you get a disinterested kid engaged in school and learning? (<em>Hint:</em> It\'s probably not what you think.)</li>\n<li>How can you help an anxious child relax for better learning?</li>\n<li>What sure-fire ways can you help a struggling child get caught up in math or reading — and have FUN while you\'re at it?</li>\n<li>How can you get your gifted child\'s needs met?</li>\n<li>What can you do to help kids develop social skills — even if dealing with people isn\'t <em>your</em> best thing?</li>\n<li>What’s the most effective way to empower children for a successful life? (<em>Hint</em>: This is also probably not what you think.) And much more!</li>\n<li><strong>BONUS: You\'ll find your own skills improving and your views more empowering—right along with your kids!</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Jacqueline Frischknecht, PhD and mother of three, and I, Trish Wilkinson, mother of two and veteran teacher, are excited to share with you what we’ve learned through thousands of hours of experience and ongoing research. On the <a href=\"/blog.html\">Brain Stages blog</a>, you\'ll find out how brains work, practical ways to enjoy kids more and stress less, and how to optimize situations as well as solve problems.</p>\n<p>Even Better, <strong><em>Bra</em><em>in Stages: How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K – 5</em></strong>, our grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years, will be available November 13, 2018 to make your life with kids a lot easier and way more pleasant!</p>\n<p><strong>Please consider joining our community of people who want to make the world a better place for kids and parents by clicking the box at the bottom of this page to get exclusive tips.</strong></p>\n<p>To learn the surprising way Brain Stages came to be, click <a href=\"/blog/too-much-coincidence-not-to-be-part-of-the-cosmic-plan\">here.</a><br />To find out more about the <em>Brain Stages</em> book, click <a href=\"/book.html\">here.</a></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #1f1f1f;\">Thanks for visiting!</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"color: #1f1f1f;\">-Trish Wilkinson</span></p>\n</div>\n\n<!-- wp:gallery -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-2 is-cropped\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://thebrainstages.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/jackie_headshot.jpeg\" alt=\"Jackie\" data-id=\"100\" data-link=\"https://thebrainstages.com/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/jackie_headshot/\" class=\"wp-image-100\"/><figcaption>Jackie</figcaption></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://thebrainstages.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/trish_headshot.jpeg\" alt=\"Trish\" data-id=\"101\" data-link=\"https://thebrainstages.com/about-brain-stages-brain-stages/trish_headshot/\" class=\"wp-image-101\"/><figcaption>Trish</figcaption></figure></li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->', 'About Brain Stages', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '22-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:00:55', '2018-10-10 20:00:55', '', 22, 'https://thebrainstages.com/2018/10/10/22-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
