(130, 1, '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\"><em><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Brain Stages</span></em>\n<span style=\"color: #515151; font-size: medium;\"><em><strong>How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K–5</strong></em></span></h2>\n<div>\n<div style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"></div>\n\n<hr class=\"styled-hr\" style=\"width: 100%;\">\n\n<div style=\"height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n\nWho says kids don’t come with instructions?\n\nWe’re pleased to announce the first edition of&nbsp;<em>Brain Stages</em>, a comprehensive grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years.\n\n​Written in a friendly, conversational style,&nbsp;this book gives you useful tools to boost your kids’ brainpower and help them develop social skills, laying the foundation for&nbsp;them to&nbsp;become&nbsp;happy, successful adults.\n\nBacked by research and experience and filled with fun games, insider information, and amazing life hacks for raising kids,&nbsp;<em>Brain Stages</em> invites parents and caregivers to enjoy kids more&nbsp;and&nbsp;stress less&nbsp;while&nbsp;bringing up well-adjusted humans.\n\n“Finally, a guide to help your child enjoy learning based upon the latest brain research and explained by a veteran teacher, who offers parents fun, practical strategies.”\n— <strong>S. Craddu</strong><strong>ck, Licensed Educational Psychologist</strong>​\n\n</div>', 'The Brain Stages Book', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '2018-10-10 20:38:24', '', 20, 'https://thebrainstages.com/2018/10/10/20-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(131, 1, '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '<h2 class=\"wsite-content-title\"><em><span style=\"font-size: xx-large;\">Brain Stages</span></em><br /><span style=\"color: #515151; font-size: medium;\"><em><strong>How to Raise Smart, Confident Kids and Have Fun Doing It, K–5</strong></em></span></h2>\n<div>\n<div style=\"height: 0px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"> </div>\n<hr class=\"styled-hr\" style=\"width: 100%;\" />\n<div style=\"height: 20px; overflow: hidden; width: 100%;\"> </div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"paragraph\" style=\"text-align: left;\">\n<p>Who says kids don’t come with instructions?</p>\n<p>We’re pleased to announce the first edition of <em>Brain Stages</em>, a comprehensive grade-by-grade guide through the elementary school years.</p>\n<p>​Written in a friendly, conversational style, this book gives you useful tools to boost your kids’ brainpower and help them develop social skills, laying the foundation for them to become happy, successful adults.</p>\n<p>Backed by research and experience and filled with fun games, insider information, and amazing life hacks for raising kids, <em>Brain Stages</em> invites parents and caregivers to enjoy kids more and stress less while bringing up well-adjusted humans.</p>\n<p>“Finally, a guide to help your child enjoy learning based upon the latest brain research and explained by a veteran teacher, who offers parents fun, practical strategies.”<br />— <strong>S. Craddu</strong><strong>ck, Licensed Educational Psychologist</strong>​</p>\n</div>\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":33} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://thebrainstages.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/brainstagescover-exp4-7d-stroke_1_orig.jpg\" alt=\"Brain Stages Cover\" class=\"wp-image-33\"/><figcaption>Brain Stages Cover</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'The Brain Stages Book', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '20-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '2018-10-10 20:38:59', '', 20, 'https://thebrainstage